Day 4 – Binary Search

Today I started learning Binary Search.

At first, I understood the algorithm, but I got confused about where to use `return`. I spent some time thinking about it instead of directly looking at the answer. After thinking it through, I understood that `return` ends the function immediately, while the loop naturally ends when there are no more elements left to search.

I also understood that Binary Search only works on a sorted array.

Practice

Q1------------------------------------------

```python
arr = [1,3,5,7,9,11]

target = 7

left = 0

right = len(arr)-1

while left <= right:

    mid = (left+right) // 2

    if arr[mid] == target:

        print(mid)

        break

    elif arr[mid] > target:

        right = mid -1

    else:

        left = mid + 1
```

